1 Section 1. (1) For purposes of this section:
2 (a) Contract means any agreement between a covered institution and a
3 foreign source for the acquisition by purchase, lease, or barter of
4 property or services, for the direct benefit or use of either of the
5 parties;
6 (b) Covered institution means any public or private two-year or
7 four-year college or university having a campus or place of business in
8 Nebraska;
9 (c) Foreign source means:
10 (i) A foreign government, including an agency of a foreign
11 government;
12 (ii) A legal entity, governmental or otherwise, created solely under
13 the laws of a foreign government;
14 (iii) An individual who is not a citizen or a national of the United
15 States or a trust territory or protectorate thereof; and
16 (iv) An agent of any entity or individual described in subdivision
17 (1)(c)(i), (ii), or (iii) of this section, including a subsidiary or
18 affiliate of a foreign legal entity acting on behalf of any such entity
19 or individual; and
20 (d) Reportable funding means any contract, gift, grant, endowment,
21 award, or donation, payment in exchange for services, capital investment,
22 salary, wage, compensation fee, or other monetary exchange, including any
23 pledge, promise, agreement or expressed intention by the foreign source
24 to provide funding which exceeds fifty dollars in value or is expected to
25 exceed fifty dollars in value over the projected length of the funding
26 relationship between the covered institution and the foreign source.
27 (2)(a) Except as provided in subdivision (b) of this subsection, on
28 the first day of each calendar quarter, each covered institution shall
29 provide a report, in a manner prescribed by the Attorney General,
30 detailing all reportable funding received by the covered institution from
31 a foreign source during the previous calendar quarter to the Attorney
