1 General and electronically to the Legislature. The report shall include:
2 (i) The amount of reportable funding received;
3 (ii) A description of the type of reportable funding and the purpose
4 for such funding, including whether the reportable funding is part of an
5 ongoing relationship with the foreign source;
6 (iii) A detailed description of the foreign source providing the
7 funding, including the name and address of the entity or individual
8 providing the funding; and
9 (iv) A copy of any contract, agreement, pledge, or memorandum of
10 understanding associated with the funding.
11 (b) This section shall not require reporting of payments made to a
12 covered institution by a natural person who would otherwise qualify as a
13 foreign source for tuition or related fees to support an individual
14 enrolled or planning to attend at a covered institution.
15 (c) The Attorney General shall post the report on the Attorney
16 General's website and such report shall be available to the public.
17 (3) The Attorney General shall enforce this section. A covered
18 institution that violates this section may be subject to a civil penalty
19 imposed by the Attorney General of up to ten thousand dollars for each
20 violation and forfeiture of any reportable funding received but not
21 reported.
